      • asInputStream

        public java.io.InputStream asInputStream()
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Streams the response content. This stream must be consumed either by reading from it and calling InputStream.close(), or calling consume() to discard the contents.

        > If the response is consumed as a stream, asBytes() will return an empty array, asString() will return an empty string and both asJSONArray() and asJSONObject() will throw exceptions.

        Returns:
        an InputStream from the response content
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the stream could not be created or has already been consumed

      • getRawResponse

        public Response getRawResponse()
        Method to get the "raw" response (i.e. the underlying OkHttp3.Response object). null is return if the response was already consumed. It is the responsibility of the application to close the response after consuming it.
        Returns:
        raw response as Response
